title: "Deterministic Resolution of the Quantum State via a Discrete Prime‑Indexed Manifold"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-05-03"
url: "https://github.com/Neil-Crago/M46"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.???????"
abstract: >-
  We propose a deterministic substrate underlying the standard quantum wave function. By re-placing the continuous complex amplitude with a discrete triadic state vector S(A) = (T total, Egrid, φgeom), we show that quantum phase evolution corresponds to a cyclic accumulation of binding error modulo the hydrogen mass unit. The transition from an uncohered state to a finalized outcome is governed by a discrete manifold M46 containing 12 prime‑indexed attractors. We demonstrate that the absence of a true midpoint between sequential primes enforces an intrinsic asymmetry that eliminates stochastic collapse. The resulting deterministic "Proximity Snap" selects the nearest prime anchor, providing a physically computable mechanism for state finalization. This framework yields a finite, quantized phase bandwidth of 60 units and resolves the measurement problem without invoking intrinsic randomness.

keywords:
